originalSql:
WITH RevenueData AS (
    SELECT 
        n.n_name AS nation_name,
        SUM(l.l_extendedprice * (1 - l.l_discount)) AS total_revenue,
        COUNT(DISTINCT o.o_orderkey) AS total_orders
    FROM 
        nation n
    JOIN 
        supplier s ON n.n_nationkey = s.s_nationkey
    JOIN 
        partsupp ps ON s.s_suppkey = ps.ps_suppkey
    JOIN 
        part p ON ps.ps_partkey = p.p_partkey
    JOIN 
        lineitem l ON p.p_partkey = l.l_partkey
    JOIN 
        orders o ON l.l_orderkey = o.o_orderkey
    WHERE 
        o.o_orderdate >= DATE '1996-01-01' AND o.o_orderdate < DATE '1997-01-01'
    GROUP BY 
        n.n_name
),
TieredRevenue AS (
    SELECT 
        nation_name,
        total_revenue,
        total_orders,
        CASE 
            WHEN total_revenue >= 1000000 THEN 'High'
            WHEN total_revenue >= 500000 THEN 'Medium'
            ELSE 'Low'
        END AS revenue_tier
    FROM 
        RevenueData
)
SELECT 
    revenue_tier,
    COUNT(nation_name) AS nation_count,
    AVG(total_revenue) AS avg_revenue,
    SUM(total_orders) AS total_orders_aggregated
FROM 
    TieredRevenue
GROUP BY 
    revenue_tier
ORDER BY 
    revenue_tier DESC

FROM (SELECT CASE WHEN SUM("s1"."l_extendedprice" * (1 - "s1"."l_discount")) >= 1000000.0000 THEN 'High  ' WHEN SUM("s1"."l_extendedprice" * (1 - "s1"."l_discount")) >= 500000.0000 THEN 'Medium' ELSE 'Low   ' END AS "REVENUE_TIER", SUM("s1"."l_extendedprice" * (1 - "s1"."l_discount")) AS "TOTAL_REVENUE", COUNT(DISTINCT "orders"."o_orderkey") AS "TOTAL_ORDERS"
FROM "nation"
INNER JOIN "supplier" ON "nation"."n_nationkey" = "supplier"."s_nationkey"
INNER JOIN "partsupp" ON "supplier"."s_suppkey" = "partsupp"."ps_suppkey"
INNER JOIN "part" ON "partsupp"."ps_partkey" = "part"."p_partkey"
INNER JOIN "s1" ON "part"."p_partkey" = "s1"."l_partkey"
INNER JOIN "orders" ON "s1"."l_orderkey" = "orders"."o_orderkey"
WHERE "orders"."o_orderdate" >= DATE '1996-01-01' AND "orders"."o_orderdate" < DATE '1997-01-01'
GROUP BY "nation"."n_name") AS "t3"
GROUP BY "t3"."REVENUE_TIER"
ORDER BY "t3"."REVENUE_TIER" DESC NULLS FIRST

SELECT COALESCE("o_orderkey", "o_orderkey") AS "o_orderkey", "o_custkey", "o_orderstatus", "o_totalprice", "o_orderdate", "o_orderpriority", "o_clerk", "o_shippriority", "o_comment"
FROM "orders"

SELECT COALESCE("t3"."REVENUE_TIER", "t3"."REVENUE_TIER") AS "REVENUE_TIER", COUNT(*) AS "NATION_COUNT", AVG("t3"."TOTAL_REVENUE") AS "AVG_REVENUE", SUM("t3"."TOTAL_ORDERS") AS "TOTAL_ORDERS_AGGREGATED"
FROM (SELECT CASE WHEN SUM("lineitem"."l_extendedprice" * (1 - "lineitem"."l_discount")) >= 1000000.0000 THEN 'High  ' WHEN SUM("lineitem"."l_extendedprice" * (1 - "lineitem"."l_discount")) >= 500000.0000 THEN 'Medium' ELSE 'Low   ' END AS "REVENUE_TIER", SUM("lineitem"."l_extendedprice" * (1 - "lineitem"."l_discount")) AS "TOTAL_REVENUE", COUNT(DISTINCT "s1"."o_orderkey") AS "TOTAL_ORDERS"
FROM "nation"
INNER JOIN "supplier" ON "nation"."n_nationkey" = "supplier"."s_nationkey"
INNER JOIN "partsupp" ON "supplier"."s_suppkey" = "partsupp"."ps_suppkey"
INNER JOIN "part" ON "partsupp"."ps_partkey" = "part"."p_partkey"
INNER JOIN "lineitem" ON "part"."p_partkey" = "lineitem"."l_partkey"
INNER JOIN "s1" ON "lineitem"."l_orderkey" = "s1"."o_orderkey"
WHERE "s1"."o_orderdate" >= DATE '1996-01-01' AND "s1"."o_orderdate" < DATE '1997-01-01'
GROUP BY "nation"."n_name") AS "t3"
GROUP BY "t3"."REVENUE_TIER"
ORDER BY "t3"."REVENUE_TIER" DESC NULLS FIRST
